snippet: If Charlie Beljan was nervous playing with Phil Mickelson and Ernie Els on Saturday, it didn't show in his score. He carded a three-under-par 68, four strokes better than Mickelson and five strokes ahead of Els.

headline.main: In Awe of Star Playing Partners, Beljan Goes On to Beat Them
